## NLP Models: Training & Fine-tuning

### Intent Classifier

The intent classifier uses `SetFit` for few-shot fine-tuning on legal domain labels. To retrain or extend it:

```bash
# Prepare labeled data
python scripts/prepare_intent_data.py --input data/raw/ --output data/training/intent/

# Fine-tune
python scripts/train_intent_classifier.py \
  --model sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2 \
  --data data/training/intent/ \
  --output models/intent/

# Evaluate
python scripts/evaluate_intent.py --model models/intent/
```

Training data format (`data/training/intent/train.jsonl`):
```json
{"text": "My employer hasn't paid me in 3 weeks", "label": "labor_law"}
{"text": "I received a court summons for debt collection", "label": "civil_law"}
```

### Adding a New Jurisdiction

1. Add procedure documents to `data/corpora/<jurisdiction>/`
2. Register the jurisdiction in `backend/nlp/retrieval/jurisdictions.py`
3. Rebuild the index: `python scripts/build_index.py --jurisdiction <name>`
4. Add test cases in `tests/unit/test_jurisdictions.py`

